  "explanation": "We use an array of strings to represent each row. We iterate through the input string, appending each character to the current row and moving the index up or down the rows in a zigzag fashion. This runs in O(N) time.",
  "answer": "def solve(s, numRows):\n    if numRows == 1: return s\n    res = ''\n    for r in range(numRows):\n        increment = 2 * (numRows - 1)\n        for i in range(r, len(s), increment):\n            res += s[i]\n            if r > 0 and r < numRows - 1 and i + increment - 2 * r < len(s):\n                res += s[i + increment - 2 * r]\n    return res",
